      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1469941533,
      "post_id" : 35450578,
      "comment_id" : 64741454,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "You are correct the versionCode must be increased on each release. However, not at development time before a release. Also, you should be able to install an apk with the same versionCode on top of an already installed apk (without uninstalling). My hunch is the problem was the resource referenced versionCode - see: <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/14946938/431296\">stackoverflow.com/a/14946938/431296</a>"
    } ],
